<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFF7FFD6A5CDFA851FB4F956" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5CDFA851AB0FAB7" blockId="7.[136,1167,1372,1399]" box="[136,1167,1372,1399]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFF7FFD6A5CDFA851AB0FAB7" box="[136,1167,1372,1399]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="4">
1.1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF7FFD6A5FCFA851DDCFAB7" authority="(Gillies &amp; Hooker ex Hooker) Troncoso (1962: 527)" authorityName="Troncoso" authorityPageNumber="527" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="Gillies &amp; Hooker ex Hooker" box="[185,995,1372,1399]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gratissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5FCFA851FB1FAB6" bold="true" box="[185,398,1372,1399]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aloysia gratissima</emphasis>
(Gillies &amp; Hooker ex Hooker) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A7A9FA841DDCFAB7" author="Troncoso, N. S." box="[748,995,1372,1399]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="527 - 531" refId="ref39694" refString="Troncoso, N. S. (1962) Notas taxonomicas sobre Verbenaceas argentinas. Darwiniana 12: 527 - 531." type="journal article" year="1962">Troncoso (1962: 527)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. (Figs. 1B, 5A)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5CDFA7D1FB4F956" blockId="7.[136,1452,1444,2083]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Shrubs 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A598FA7D1F07FA7F" box="[221,312,1444,1471]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5‒3 m</quantity>
high, tetragonal branches, puberulous. Leaves opposite, often fasciculate, petiole 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A18EFA7D1B17FA7F" box="[1227,1320,1444,1471]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2‒3 mm</quantity>
long; blade 0.8‒2.2 × 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A5B9FA111F43FA23" box="[252,380,1480,1507]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3‒0.5 cm</quantity>
, chartaceous, elliptical to ovate, apex acute to obtuse, base cuneate or attenuate, margin entire, ciliate, adaxial surface strigose, abaxial surface glabrescent, main vein conspicuous, prominent in the adaxial surface. Inflorescences 1 per axil, 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A4E3F9C91C1CF9EB" box="[422,547,1552,1579]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.15" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="6.15" valueMax="8.5" valueMin="3.8">3.8‒8.5 cm</quantity>
long, peduncle 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A791F9C91D03F9EB" box="[724,828,1552,1579]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="0.85" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.7">0.7‒1 cm</quantity>
long, pubescent, rachis pubescent; bracts 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A055F9C91B52F9EB" box="[1296,1389,1552,1579]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1‒2 mm</quantity>
long, elliptical, abaxial surface strigose, glandular sessile trichomes present, margin ciliate; calyx 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A1C0F9ED1AC8F98F" box="[1157,1271,1588,1615]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.0">2‒3.5 mm</quantity>
long, externally hispid-canescent, glandular sessile trichomes present; corolla 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A604F9811DA0F9B3" box="[833,927,1624,1651]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4‒5 mm</quantity>
long, white. Fruit 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF7FFD6A137F9811ADAF9B3" box="[1138,1253,1624,1651]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.2">1.2‒2 mm</quantity>
long, surrounded by the persistent calyx.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFF7FFD9A5F8F9791D46FE51" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5F8F9791F6DF8AF" blockId="7.[136,1452,1444,2083]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5F8F9791C33F97A" bold="true" box="[189,524,1696,1722]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF7FFD6A749F9791CDEF97A" authorityName="Troncoso" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="Gillies &amp; Hooker ex Hooker" box="[524,737,1696,1722]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gratissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A749F9791CDEF97A" box="[524,737,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aloysia gratissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most widely distributed species of the genus, found in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF7FFD6A5CDF91D1F1DF91E" box="[136,290,1732,1758]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">United States</collectingCountry>
, north of 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF7FFD6A4D4F91D1FD6F91E" box="[401,489,1732,1758]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and South America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A79BF91D1D87F91E" author="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J." box="[734,952,1732,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="193 - 212" refId="ref36202" refString="Moroni, P., O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J. (2016) Species delimitation in the Aloysia gratissima complex (Verbenaceae) following the phylogenetic species concept. Botanical journal of the Linnean Society 180: 193 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / boj. 12369" type="journal article" year="2016">
Moroni 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A679F91C1D49F91E" box="[828,886,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A16EF91C1A5AF91E" box="[1067,1125,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016). In 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF7FFD6A198F91D1B1BF91E" box="[1245,1316,1732,1758]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, the species can be found in the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A421F9311FFCF8C2" box="[356,451,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cerrado</emphasis>
, Atlantic Forest, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF7FFD6A7F7F9301D3EF8C2" box="[690,769,1769,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Pampa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A7F7F9301D3EF8C2" box="[690,769,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
domains, from 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFF7FFD6A6F7F9311DCCF8C2" box="[946,1011,1768,1794]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bahia</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFF7FFD6A153F9311AD9F8C2" box="[1046,1254,1768,1794]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
states (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A07CF9311F07F8E6" author="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref36092" refString="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. (2020 a) Aloysia in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15122 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Moroni &amp; O’Leary 2020a</bibRefCitation>
). In the 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFF7FFD6A4D0F8D51C4CF8E7" box="[405,627,1804,1831]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Espírito Santo state</collectingRegion>
, it occurs in disturbed habitats near to 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A16FF8D51A8BF8E6" box="[1066,1204,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">quilombolas</emphasis>
areas, in the seasonal semideciduous forest and dense rainforest, supposedly related to naturalization due to cultivation. Not found inside SPAs in this state.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5F8F8A11BAFF852" blockId="7.[136,1452,1444,2083]" box="[189,1424,1912,1939]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5F8F8A11F60F852" bold="true" box="[189,351,1912,1938]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Collected with flowers in May, July, September, October, and November and with fruits in July.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5F8F8451B50F81A" blockId="7.[136,1452,1444,2083]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5F8F8451CBDF876" bold="true" box="[189,642,1948,1974]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Preliminary conservation assessment:</emphasis>
—This a common species with a wide distribution (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A188F8451B98F876" author="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J." box="[1229,1447,1948,1974]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="193 - 212" refId="ref36202" refString="Moroni, P., O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J. (2016) Species delimitation in the Aloysia gratissima complex (Verbenaceae) following the phylogenetic species concept. Botanical journal of the Linnean Society 180: 193 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / boj. 12369" type="journal article" year="2016">
Moroni 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A06EF8441B5AF876" box="[1323,1381,1948,1974]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5ABF8181F19F81A" box="[238,294,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016), and occurs inside PAs in South America. Considered “Least Concern” (LC) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A19CF8191B5CF81A" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[1241,1379,1984,2010]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref34955" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 30 December 2019)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD9A5F8F83D1D7CFF1C" blockId="7.[136,1452,1444,2083]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1452,158,401]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5F8F83D1F8EF83E" bold="true" box="[189,433,2020,2046]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Selected material:—</emphasis>
